# Reinstalled / regenerated inside the build — never ship host artifacts.
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.turbo
**/coverage
**/generated
**/*.tsbuildinfo
# Local Python virtualenvs (e.g. agent-service/.venv) carry broken `bin/python` symlinks that
# docker.exe's context transfer rejects, and never belong in a Node image.
**/.venv
**/venv

# The top-level typecheck-only `agent/` workspace member (M2-C1 cold-start dataset gen) is not a
# dependency of any image built from this context (tenant-runtime, control-plane). The Dockerfiles
# don't install its devDeps, so a whole-workspace `turbo run build` fails trying to typecheck it
# ("Cannot find type definition file for 'jest'/'node'"). Excluding the dir from the build context
# drops it from pnpm's workspace resolution so turbo skips it — the images never needed it.
/agent

# VCS + editor
.git
.gitignore
.vscode
.idea

# Secrets: keep .env out of the image; the example is harmless but unneeded.
**/.env
**/.env.*

# Local infra + logs
*.log
docker-compose.yml
README.md

# WSL symlinks: every CLAUDE.md is a symlink → AGENTS.md, which docker.exe's build context
# transfer rejects ("invalid file request CLAUDE.md"). Excluded per the repo CLAUDE.md's
# "Python/ML services & docker.exe" note; also unneeded in any image.
**/CLAUDE.md
